{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KqVEByiuLwbqj9ranqWeSe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had `write` and `read` permissions on the `/app` vhost but was missing `configure` permission. RabbitMQ requires `configure` to declare (create) a queue — even if it already exists, the AMQP `queue.declare` call checks configure permission.\n\n**Fix:** `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — granted full configure/write/read to `app-user` on `/app`.\n\n**Verified state:**\n- `app-producer` — `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts\n- `app-queue` — type `classic`, durable, 8 messages (and growing)\n- `/app` vhost — exists, permissions correct\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes — `Running`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":688,"cache_read_input_tokens":32953,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":688},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"502c3033-22ea-4b23-a5d5-ee658e2ad95b","uuid":"81ab2f0b-8979-4e96-98c8-607c55979786","request_id":"req_011CcdFvriewCJgWGm2bNM35"}
